[On top of USA's (experimental) and Russia's (likely, commercial) veterinary SARS-CoV-2 vaccines, an experimental vaccine has been produced in Finland, recently permitted for controlled field use in mink (see item 2).

China, the world's leading mink producer, has -- so far -- not reported SARS-CoV-2 cases/infections in its massive mink population, and no information about the application of animal vaccines has become there publicly available. However, the following excerpt from a scientific paper published in March 2021 (citation below), includes the following information: "We further found that a spike protein-based subunit vaccine largely prevented SARS-CoV-2 replication and lung damage caused by SARS-CoV-2 infection in minks. Our study indicates that minks are a useful animal model for evaluating the efficacy of drugs or vaccines against COVID-19 and that vaccination is a potential strategy to prevent minks from transmitting SARS-CoV-2."

Further information is anticipated.

Citation: Shuai L, Zhong G, Yuan Q, et al. Replication, pathogenicity, and transmission of SARS-CoV-2 in minks. National Science Review. 2021; 8(3): nwaa291; https://doi.org/10.1093/nsr/nwaa291. - Mod.AS

